ons":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"one of a pair"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"spouse, mate, partner; husband","examples":[{"text":"قَدْ سَمِعَ ٱللَّٰهُ قَوْلَ ٱلَّتِي تُجَادِلُكَ فِي زَوْجِهَا وَتَشْتَكِي إِلَى ٱللَّٰهِ وَٱللَّٰهُ يَسْمَعُ تَحَاوُرَكُمَا إِنَّ ٱللَّٰهَ سَمِيعٌ بَصِيرٌ","english":"God has certainly heard the speech of her who pleads with you about her husband and complains to God. God hears the conversation between the two of you."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"spouse, mate, partner; wife","tags":["feminine"],"examples":[{"text":"فَقُلْنَا يَا آدَمُ إِنَّ هَٰذَا عَدُوٌّ لَّكَ وَلِزَوْجِكَ فَلَا يُخْرِجَنَّكُمَا مِنَ ٱلْجَنَّةِ فَتَشْقَىٰ","english":"We said, “O Adam! This is indeed an enemy of yours and your mate’s. So do not let him expel you from paradise, or you will be miserable.”"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a pair or couple","examples":[{"text":"هُمَا زَوْجَانِ","english":"They two are a pair or couple."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"kind, type","tags":["archaic"],"examples":[{"text":"إِذَا رُجَّتِ الْأَرْضُ رَجًّا وَبُسَّتِ الْجِبَالُ بَسًّا فَكَانَتْ هَبَاءً مُّنْبَثًّا وَكُنتُمْ أَزْوَاجًا ثَلَاثَةً فَأَصْحَابُ الْمَيْمَنَةِ مَا أَصْحَابُ الْمَيْمَنَةِ وَأَصْحَابُ الْمَشْأَمَةِ مَا أَصْحَابُ الْمَشْأَمَةِ وَالسَّابِقُونَ السَّابِقُونَ","english":"When the earth is shaken with convulsion / And the mountains are crushed, crumbling / And become dust dispersing / And ye become of three kinds: Then the companions of the right – what are the companions of the right? And the companions of the left – what are the companions of the left? And the forerunners, the forerunners!"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to marry off, to give in marriage","tags":["ditransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to pair, to couple, to join in pairs"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to double, to geminate"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Aramaic זוגא (zawgā, “yoke, pair”), from Ancient Greek ζεῦγος (zeûgos, “yoke”) which was used in Greek for the yoke of marriage – now it forms a root ز و ج (z w j).\n\nDenominal verb derived from زَوْج (zawj, “pair”)."},"ipa":["/zawd͡ʒ/","/zaw.wa.d͡ʒa/"]}